# Build prod project for private npm packages
Go to Linux environment such as Putty(https://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/latest.html).

Install NodeJs 16.15.0, Yarn 1.22.17, Npm and Git.

Clone repo https://github.com/GudniPallGudnason/iabtcf-es.git

Checkout branch ch-1.5.6

Install packages with yarn install

Build project with yarn build

Move files from Linux environment to your device, fetch files from modules/{cmpapi/cli/core}/lib, if Linux environment is Putty then get pscp from (https://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/latest.html)
And download files with this command for each module:
pscp -r -i C:\Git\pkey.ppk root@51.159.234.1:/root/gudni/iabtcf-es/modules/cli/lib/* C:\Git\pscpfiles\cli

# Create private npm package
Create package.json
npm init

Create private git repo
https://github.com/new

Create Token
https://github.com/settings/tokens
Create repo, workflow og write:packages, have every thing checked in the categories

# Publish package
npm login -registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
username:<github username>
password:<token>
email:<github email>

Go to package dir

Remember to increase the version number

npm publish

# Use private npm package

Create .npmrc file in project using the package, the file contains:
@cookiehub-com:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=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

Add the dependencies in the package.json
"dependencies": {
    "@cookiehub-com/iabtcf-core": "^1.0.0",
    "@cookiehub-com/iabtcf-cli": "^1.0.0",
    "@cookiehub-com/iabtcf-cmpapi": "^1.0.0"
  }